text.section:
Subject to the authority of the Commission, the Board of Trustees may:
Establish entrance requirements for the College;
Approve courses and programs;
Adopt and change curricula;
Establish and change requirements for the awarding of credits and degrees and for graduation;
Work with the Commission to establish cooperative program agreements that qualify as statewide programs in accordance with § 16-310(d) of this title; and
Develop effective relationships and cooperative programs with the Baltimore City Public School System to assure that high school students are encouraged to enroll in the College.
